<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The family is ordained of God. Marriage between a man and woman is essential to His eternal plan. Children are entitled to birth within the bonds of matrimony and to be reared by a father and mother who honor marital vows with complete fidelity.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Okay so bastard children are being slighted according to this and most xians would probably agree, but what implications does this decree have for babies born outside the &quot;bonds of matrimony&quot;? Are they forever disadvantaged? What if their parents stay together but don't legally marry?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Happiness in family life is most likely to be achieved when founded upon the teachings of Jesus Christ.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
